# How to Deploy This Azure Static Website

## 1. Create a Storage Account in Azure
- Go to the [Azure Portal](https://portal.azure.com).
- Navigate to **Storage Accounts** and click **Create**.
- Fill in subscription, resource group, unique storage account name, and region.
- Click **Review + create** and then **Create**.

## 2. Enable Static Website Hosting
- Open your new storage account.
- In the left menu, click **Static website** under **Data management**.
- Set **Static website** to **Enabled**.
- Enter `index.html` as the Index document name.
- Enter `error.html` as the Error document path.
- Click **Save** (this creates a special `$web` container).

## 3. Upload Website Files
- Go to **Containers**, then open the `$web` container.
- Upload your website files (`index.html`, `error.html`, `style.css`, images, etc.) from this repository.

## 4. Access Your Deployed Website
- Go back to the **Static website** settings.
- Copy the **Primary endpoint** URL.
- Open the URL in your browser to see your deployed static site.
- Visit a non-existent page to test your custom error page.
